  "prompt": "Is it okay for an Indian to travel from USA to India via Brussels with expired US visa?",
  "response": "No, it is **not okay** for an Indian citizen to travel from the USA to India via Brussels with an expired US visa. Here's why:\n\n*   **Expired US Visa Validity:** While you might be leaving the US, an expired US visa typically indicates your permission to *enter* the US has lapsed. It doesn't usually affect your ability to *depart* the US.\n\n*   **Transit Through Brussels (Schengen Area):**  This is the critical part. Brussels is in Belgium, which is part of the Schengen Area.  When transiting through a Schengen area airport, you generally remain under Schengen immigration control *unless* you stay in the international transit zone.\n\n    *   **Staying in the International Transit Zone (most likely scenario):**  To stay in the international transit zone of a Schengen airport, *without* needing a visa, you typically need a valid visa *for your final destination* (India, in this case) *and* meet specific requirements depending on your nationality (Indian in this case). **Having an expired US visa generally does not meet the requirements for visa-free transit through the Schengen area.**\n    *   **Leaving the Airport (less likely scenario):**  If you need to leave the airport for any reason (e.g., a very long layover that requires an overnight stay in a hotel), you *will* need a Schengen visa, regardless of your US visa status.\n\n*   **Airline Responsibility:** Airlines are responsible for ensuring passengers have the correct documents to enter or transit through their destinations. They will likely deny you boarding for the flight from the US to Brussels if you don't meet Schengen visa requirements.\n\n**In Summary:**\n\nAn expired US visa does *not* grant you any special privileges or allowances to transit through the Schengen area.  **You will likely need a Schengen visa to transit through Brussels.**  Contact the Belgian embassy or consulate in the US to determine if you need a transit visa or a full Schengen visa for your layover.  If a visa is required, apply well in advance of your travel date.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Check specific requirements:**  Always check the specific transit visa requirements for Belgium (or any other Schengen country you might transit through) on the official website of the Belgian embassy or consulate in the US, or the Belgian immigration authorities.  These rules can change.\n*   **Indian Passport:**  While you are an Indian citizen, the entry requirements for Indian citizens traveling to Belgium and transiting through Schengen are specific and are not waived simply because you previously held a US visa.\n*   **Contact the Airline:** Contact the airline you are flying with (e.g., Brussels Airlines) to confirm their requirements for transit passengers in Brussels.\n\n**Do not assume it will be okay.  Verify and apply for a Schengen visa if necessary.**  You risk being denied boarding and significant disruption to your travel plans.\n",
